The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Kothari for world meet
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Kothari for world meet
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Sourav Kothari will represent India in the forthcoming IBSF World Snooker Championship to be held in Wels, Austria from Monday.         
	Besides, Pankaj Advani and Manan Chandra, the 24-year old city lad was included in the Indian contingent for the 12-day long world meet. Souravs entry as the third player from the country was accepted in the eleventh hour by the International Billiards amp; Snooker Federation (IBSF) after the persistent efforts of the Billiards amp; Snooker Federation of India (BSFI) president, Captain P.V.K. Mohan.         
	While Geet Sethi and Alok Kumar will represent the country in the masters event (above 40) category, current national champion Vidya Pillai and Anuja Chandra will be vying for top honours in the womens category. In the mens category, about 112 players from more than 45 countries are scheduled to participate while 30 players from 19 countries will be partaking in the ladies event.         
	The Indian contingent with national coach Subhash B. Agarwal will leave on Saturday.                                                                                                                          
